We’ve got something super fresh coming tomorrow. Imperf x Legendary Tattoo Artist @tannerramsey. He’s an even better human than artist, which is wildly radical. Stay tuned, keep those eyes 👀 peeled and don’t scroll too quick. 

Our community gets early access today at 12pm PT so if you want the VIP treatment, sign up to receive our emails. Link in bio. 🤙🏽

#imperfects #thehumanexperience

“When this opportunity to work with Imperfects presented itself, it was great to see another strong company coming out of my hometown. San Diego birthed a ton of amazing skate brands ever since I was a kid. Once I really looked into Imperfects and realized their vision and the strength of their company it was a no-brainer to work with them. 

The graphic for the board was inspired a lot by older graphics done by some of my favorites that Mark Gonzales, Neil Blender, and Ed Templeton did.”

-Tanner Ramsey

Tanner Ramsey x Imperfects deck is now live! Go check it out.

Tune by Tanner’s lil bro @griffin.wins
Shot by Mason Poole on super 8 film

#imperfects #thehumanexperience #handmade

"I have a love for crude offset printing and was able to achieve that with this graphic. I really enjoy the rough loose design work. I’m interested in color, blocking, rough line work, and the use of mixed media. At times I feel like I have to be so tight with my tattooing, that when I paint I’m able to be a lot more relaxed and free. It’s a time that coloring outside the lines actually works."

-Tanner Ramsey

Our only dream with our skateboards is to make sure they offer a clear mindset for their users and a fresh canvas for the artists we work with. Mission accomplished on this one. 

Tanner Ramsey x Imperfects live now. Hit the link.

✨SHOW ANNOUNCEMENT✨
Opening September 16 is our next show, What Came First, featuring Tanner Ramsey and Jack Watts. 

Growing up in Santa Barbara, I was surrounded by some incredibly talented artists, which constantly challenged me to do and make more. One of the folks that made a lasting impact and truly helped me find my passion for tattoos and curation was @tannerramsey. Even as we started conceptualizing this gallery, I knew Tanner was someone we wanted to work with. We were happy to hear @tattoosforyourenemies was working alongside Tanner (and the other wonderful folks) at @nathans_lounge and jumped at the opportunity to bring this joint show to life. With such unique perspectives of traditional tattoo imagery, their immaculate detail and execution, and incredibly kind souls, I couldn’t be more excited to share their latest body of work shown in “What Came First.”

We will be hosting an opening reception on September 16 from, from 5 - 10 PM. We’ll have tunes and drinks available and we can’t wait to celebrate with you all.

The show will be on view from September 16 - October 15. 

With gratitude,
Ben

A look into “What Came First.” We’re incredibly excited to share our next show and the work of Tanner Ramsey and Jack Watts. Their work speak volumes and their interpersonal friendship is embodied within their creations.

Tanner says, “When Ben asked me to do a show I immediately thought of taking that opportunity to create a body of work with my friend and coworker, Jack Watts. We spent the summer collaborating and discussing alternative ways to approach our ideas. 
 
We wanted to build a show that was different than anything we had ever done before. Both of us becoming fathers in the last few years inspired us to reimagine the world through youthful eyes. With subject matter that first shaped our imagination, the pieces in the show hold a lot of childhood nostalgia and wonder.

There are repurposed found objects, installations, visual representations of interests and a strong use of collaborative thinking. 

We have gotten to explore new mediums, challenge our creative energy, and above all else hang out.” 

Join us for the opening reception on September 16th @wantsneedsventura 

Photos by @kelleramsey

This original piece will be available to buy opening night (September 16th from 5 - 10pm), as well as archival prints of the What Came First show poster.

A peek in the studio with @tattoosforyourenemies and @tannerramsey while they prepare for ‘What Came First.’ We’re incredibly eager to see you all this Saturday for the premiere of this next show!

Photo by @kelleramsey

Tanner Ramsey grew up in Carlsbad, CA a small beach town in San Diego. He is now living and working in Los Angeles tattooing at @nathans_lounge in Echo Park. 

Tanner grew up in a large family as the eldest of six kids. His mother filled his home with love, art & music. His families limited resources never affected the creative drive in the household. 

Before starting tattooing, Tanner had a hand in sewing, painting, printmaking, and many other mediums made available through the guidance of family members. As he journeyed into the art world, trying different mediums through trial and error, tattooing became his focus and joy. 

After working in corporate fashion, Tanner and his wife decided to move to Ventura to chase their dreams of being full time artists. Tanner was able to find an apprenticeship in Ventura under a handful of amazing tattooers, one of them being his mentor Joe Romero. 

Joe Romero passed soon after Tanner finished his apprenticeship which didn’t lead him to slow down, yet instead pushed him harder to work at his craft and shape a career in tattooing and the arts. 

Ventura was Tanner’s home for 11 years and built the foundation of his life as an artist. The community here in Ventura supported him, allowed to him opportunity to reach goals, and always showed up for him, even after moving to Los Angeles 4 years ago.

Tanner has a desire to explore different mediums and continue the trial and error process that he has come to find comfort in. 

Photo by @kelleramsey.

Setting my intentions for this next year, I am going to be more vulnerable, give more light to things I am proud of, feel more, explore more, give more time to things that are important to me, don’t seek approval, be present, laugh more, allow growth in my parenting, share love and respect, continue to put more&more value on my family time, don’t try to be someone I think people want me to be, nourish friendships, be extremely grateful for the people that see value in me, create, create, create. For all of you wonderful people that have read this far, please take this next year to invest in yourself, and give time to your passions.
